  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN Secretary-General&apos;s Change Support Team (CCST)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The UN Secretary-General&apos;s activities on climate change can be supported by funding the SG&apos;s Climate Change Support Team (CCST). As a significant result, the SG can play a pro-active role in ensuring successful climate negotiations in Copenhagen and increasing the awareness on climate change. The SG-led coherent UN System will be recognized as an effective partner in climate activities and climate change issues will be mainstreamed into relevant processes and development plans. According to the Finnish Development Policy, Finland promotes the cooperation to combat climate change. Finland endorses the United Nations&apos; role as the most important actor in international development policy and support for CCST contributes to that goal. In the year 2009, CCST&apos;s activities are funded with 200 000 Euros.</narrative>
  </description>
